:2480x1600/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73339180/ocean_windows_open.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Fisker</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"HFiiyt\">Fisker has another braking issue on its hands, prompting US safety regulators to open a fourth probe on the automaker\u2019s electric Ocean SUV. </p>\n<p id=\"k5hRvu\">This time, the National Highway and Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA) is looking into customer claims that the Ocean would unexpectedly activate its automatic emergency braking (AEB) without any forward obstruction. <a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/business/autos-transportation/us-auto-regulator-opens-preliminary-evaluation-into-fiskers-ocean-vehicles-2024-05-10/\"><em>Reuters</em> reports</a> three of the claims involved someone getting injured.</p>\n<p id=\"yXkbbm\">This is the second probe opened for the 2023 Ocean that has to do with the ve", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/10/24153514/fisker-ocean-nhtsa-investigation-automatic-emergency-brakes", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Fisker\u2019s brakes can\u2019t catch a break", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-05-10T14:15:24+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Floating MacBook Pro on wallpaper of Mac and Safari icons, with system preferences opened and the Monterey wallpaper.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/grlqTaKqaVNQDdRQYQC_Yn7Pfus=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73339036/HT016_macOS_0003.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Samar Haddad / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"kFmUA9\">You may not spend much time thinking about the default apps you\u2019ve got set up on macOS until they suddenly get configured the wrong way \u2014 and you find that, say, the app that pops up when you click on an image file is not the one you want to use. </p>\n<p id=\"5iUsZg\">Out of the box, your Mac will use Apple\u2019s own tools for most tasks: click on a web link in Mail and you\u2019ll see Safari, for example, or double-click on an image you\u2019ve downloaded to your system and up pops Photos. However, you might want to use different apps, or maybe a freshly installed app has decided to make i", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24153045/macos-default-apps-email-browser-how-to", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to set the default apps in macOS", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-05-10T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Man eating orange while wearing Oura Ring with a render of the new cardiovascular age feature.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/MbLVPEWjZgFMPzL5GoeXhy4eFvw=/136x0:1873x1158/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73339002/BOTH_FEATURES_UI.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Cardiovascular age is a proxy for how \u201cstiff\u201d your arteries are.</em> | Image: Oura</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"8N37iS\">Oura\u2019s been busy this past year <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/6/8/23752876/oura-ring-social-circles-sleep-stage-algorithm\">launching</a> <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/3/15/23640205/oura-ring-sleep-tracking-chronotype-circadian-rhythm\">several</a> <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/31/24056193/oura-says-its-chill-about-samsungs-galaxy-ring-but-heres-a-new-stress-tracking-feature-anyway\">new</a> <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/3/24119189/oura-ring-labs-symptom-radar-wearable-smart-ring\">features</a> \u2014 and folks with th", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/10/24152827/oura-ring-cardiovascular-age-vo2-max-wearables", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Oura Ring will soon be able to gauge how \u2018old\u2019 your heart is", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-05-10T13:01:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of an iPad on top of a Vergecast logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9Gy9dkYC3JihaopfpGIwSvXm5g0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73338888/VST_0510_Site.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Alex Parkin / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"tzGMZ8\">People seem to like <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/7/24150047/apple-ipad-let-loose-event-news-announcements\">Apple\u2019s new iPad Pro</a>, with its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24091213/apple-ipad-air-2024-pro-specs-comparison\">better screen</a> and impressive design. People also seem to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/8/24152236/apple-ipad-pro-commercial-artists-ai\"><em>really </em>hate Apple\u2019s new ad</a> in which the company crushes centuries of creative tools because, in the future, there is only iPad. And after all the iPad stuff this week, people are still asking the same question: <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/2/24147271", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/10/24153097/ipad-pro-2024-apple-max-disney-bundle-foxconn-vergecast", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The beginning and end of the iPad", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-05-10T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Promotional art for Hades II.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/PSfgZrGYNd98CQpzjcVJN9wO_hY=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73338831/H2_Wallpaper_Melinoe_4k_01.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Supergiant Games</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"dwBVU1\">Now that the<em> </em><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24150249/hades-2-early-access-release-date-steam-egs\"><em>Hades II</em> early access period has started</a>, opening up a more complete but still early build of the game, I\u2019ve been fighting against the urge <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24135151/hades-2-technical-test-impressions\">to gorge myself on it</a> \u2014 and losing. To be fair, I have a weak spirit since I loved the first <em>Hades,</em> which introduced me to the concept of roguelikes, a genre I avoided out of disdain for repetition. Also, and this is the biggest factor in my spiritual war against the game: I have a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24152085/hades-2-steam-deck-performance", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Hades II is the perfect Steam Deck game", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-05-10T12:20:39+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A hand holding the silver Apple AirPods Max.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/n9VVQoo-3JlbHBpLRq-oTKXjypg=/59x0:1982x1282/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73338792/IMG_6828_3.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Apple\u2019s noise-canceling AirPods Max are $100 off for the first time since December.</em> | Photo by Becca Farsace / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"VBnmbA\">Not too long ago, it seemed like every retailer was offering a steep discount on <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22177494/apple-airpods-max-headphones-review-price-features\"><strong>Apple\u2019s AirPods Max</strong></a>. Then, suddenly, they all stopped. For the past few months, we\u2019ve rarely seen the AirPods Max drop below $500 \u2014 that is, until this week. Now, for the second time this year, you can grab Apple\u2019s on-ear headphones at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/New-Apple-AirPods-Max-Blue/dp/B08PZD76NP/?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_b", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/10/24075360/amazon-apple-airpods-max-noise-canceling-headphones-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple\u2019s AirPods Max are receiving a rare $100 discount at Amazon", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-05-10T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Several rows of wind turbines standing in the sea.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2Y-JsgZyZYZC_NWvUYnU5_QwJoQ=/0x0:7768x5179/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73338749/1815431245.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Riffgat offshore wind farm, around 15 kilometers north of the island of Borkum.</em> | Photo: Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"jwiwmv\">Data centers and offshore wind farms could prove to be a perfect pair as AI grows increasingly energy-hungry. </p>\n<p id=\"RjXPKL\">Many of the companies racing to roll out new generative AI tools have also made big commitments to rein in their greenhouse gas emissions. A rush of new AI data centers could throw those climate goals off \u2014 unless they find a clean source of energy.</p>\n<p id=\"M0gMZa\">Conveniently, some of the quirks with AI data centers make them a good match for wind farms at sea. And the offshore wind industry, which has already cozied up with Big Tech, could ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24152249/ai-data-center-renewable-energy-offshore-wind", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The answer to AI\u2019s\u00a0energy\u00a0needs could be blowing in the wind", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-05-10T10:14:33+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"ChatGPT logo in mint green and black colors.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/SZUw_21E5jKgVl7eIJiY_tbvDyg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73338594/STK149_AI_02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>OpenAI has allegedly been trying to poach Google employees to work on its own search product offering.</em> | Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"YESwuA\">OpenAI is reportedly gearing up to announce a search product powered by artificial intelligence on Monday that could threaten Google\u2019s dominance. That target date, provided to <a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/technology/openai-plans-announce-google-search-competitor-monday-sources-say-2024-05-09/\"><em>Reuters</em></a> by \u201ctwo sources familiar with the matter,\u201d would time the announcement a day before Google kicks off <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/14/24101171/google-io-2024-announced-may-14-android-ai-gemini\">its annual I/O conference</a>, which", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/10/24153421/openai-chatgpt-google-search-competitor-service-io", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "OpenAI could unveil its Google search competitor on Monday", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-05-10T00:12:28+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/vST08gFpfbf9H5S3J-aypdhC3W4=/14x0:1486x981/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73338224/20240430_Holographic_AR_Displays_N6A1077.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Stanford\u2019s holographic AR glasses prototype.</em> | Image: Andrew Brodhead / Stanford</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"MVH7yO\">A research team at Stanford is <a href=\"https://news.stanford.edu/2024/05/08/3d-augmented-reality-regular-glasses/\">developing a new AI-assisted holographic imaging technology</a> it claims is thinner, lighter, and higher quality than anything its researchers have seen. Could it take augmented reality (AR) headsets to the next level? </p>\n<p id=\"OGwNwj\">For now, the lab version has an anemic field of view \u2014 just 11.7 degrees in the lab, far smaller than a Magic Leap 2 or even a Microsoft HoloLens. </p>\n<p id=\"rKDVT1\">But Stanford\u2019s Computational Imaging Lab <a href=\"https://www.computationalimaging.org/publications/ho", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/9/24153092/stanford-ai-holographic-ar-glasses-3d-imaging-research", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Did Stanford just prototype the future of AR glasses?", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-05-10T00:09:58+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Xbox logo illustration\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VUTrCkcL8mLgzGWQCKase1COfWw=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73338220/acastro_STK048_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"E2xzYP\">Microsoft has been talking about plans for an Xbox mobile gaming store for <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/10/19/23411972/microsoft-xbox-mobile-store-games\">a couple of years now</a>, and the company now plans to launch it in July. Speaking at the Bloomberg Technology Summit earlier today, Xbox president Sarah Bond revealed the launch date and how Microsoft is going to avoid Apple\u2019s strict App Store rules.</p>\n<p id=\"nL97Xd\">\u201cWe\u2019re going to start by bringing our own first-party portfolio to [the Xbox mobile store], so you\u2019re going to see games like <em>Candy Crush </em>show up in that experience, games like <em>Minecraft,\u201d </em>says Bond<em>. \u201c</em>We\u2019re going ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/9/24153245/microsoft-xbox-mobile-gaming-store-july-launch", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Microsoft\u2019s new Xbox mobile gaming store is launching in July", "user": null, "vote": 0}]